featured_reviews.review_id:
A historical area, the shape of the building carries a wonderful decoration, a beautiful design from the inside and the outside, you can enter the top of the building with tickets for a simple, symbolic price, overlooking four streets, it is located in the middle in a circular shape around which all the markets are located, and there is another beautiful building near it. It is a large mosque with a beautiful structure , It is not allow to enter the camera or bags! This place is crowded most of the time in the evening, with the presence of different and cheap markets as well, and there are restaurants for hidden meals, a very wonderful place. If you are in Hyderabad u must visit it and buy things from there are cheaper, my journey was fantastic in this place I will share some pictures for you.
There's one thing I didn't like it around the building there are many Carriages and rugs to sell things and new days they building temple which that can't show the beauty of this place really.

featured_reviews.review_id: One of the biggest mosques of Govindpuri, Delhi. A huge mosque building just beside the red light near Govindpuri Metro Station in New Delhi. Nehru Place is not farther than 5 kms from this mosque. Attached with this mosque is a Madarsa imparting Islamic education to the students coming from different places of NCR of Delhi and Uttar Pradesh and Bihar. Despite having located very near to red light, the atmosphere in the mosque is cool, peaceful and pleasant. Good provision for ablution (wazu), urinals, toilets and bathrooms - all are available here. Regular five times prayers and Juma prayer are offered here. Eid ul Fitr and Eid ul Azha Namaz are also conducted in a magnificent manner. The mosque and the Madarsa has dedicated and sincere Committee which conducts their affairs smoothly. These are managed out of sadqa and public contributions.

featured_reviews.review_id:
A large and spacious mosque located near Govind Puri metro station. This mosque is visible from the south of both the platforms.

Very large number of people gathered here for Friday prayers regularly. Yearly Eid Mubarak and Eid-ul-Azha namaz are also arranged here.

Few Islamic festivals are also celebrated here now and then.

A madrasa is situated inside the mosque area. It is mainly for the children learning the course of Hifz (memorization of the entire holy Quran).

Nearby places include -- Banarsidas Chandiwala Estate, Govind Puri metro station, Delhi Jal board office and facilities, Giri Nagar Gurudwara, Maa Anandmoyee and Guru Ravi Das Marg crossing.
